<item>
            <title>[BEAM-12253] Read.UnboundedSourceAsSDFRestrictionTracker doesn&apos;t use cache for readers in getProgress</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-12253</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/io/Read.java#L963&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/java/core/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/io/Read.java#L963&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In getProgress, if currentReader == null a new reader is constructed from the restriction checkpoint.  I think that we should consult the reader cache as creating readers is sometimes expensive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I observed in Nexmark pipelines that readers were being created at this location.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
